<subpara id="RM0000015VV00IX_06" type-id="51" category="05">
<name>INSPECTION PROCEDURE</name>
</subpara>
<subpara id="RM0000015VV00IX_07" type-id="01" category="01">
<name>PROCEDURE</name>
<testgrp id="RM0000015VV00IX_07_0001" proc-id="RM0250U___00008JM00000">
<testtitle>CHECK OTHER DTCS OUTPUT (IN ADDITION TO DTC P0796)</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<test1>
<ptxt>Connect the intelligent tester to the DLC3.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Turn the ignition switch on (IG) and turn the intelligent tester on.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Enter the following items: "DIAGNOSIS / OBD/MOBD / ECT / DTC INFO / CURRENT CODES".</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Read the DTCs using the intelligent tester.</ptxt>
<spec>
<title>Result</title>
<table pgwide="1">
<tgroup cols="2" align="center">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="3.83in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="3.25in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Display (DTC output)</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Proceed to</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Only "P0796" is output</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>A</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
<row>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>"P0796" and other DTCs</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>B</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</spec>
</test1>
<atten4>
<ptxt>If a solenoid is stuck OFF , DTCs for several solenoids including the malfunctioning solenoid will be detected.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</content6>
<res>
<down ref="RM0000015VV00IX_07_0010" fin="false">B</down>
<right ref="RM0000015VV00IX_07_0002" fin="false">A</right>
</res>
</testgrp>
<testgrp id="RM0000015VV00IX_07_0010" proc-id="RM0250U___00009Q100000">
<testtitle>PERFORM ACTIVE TEST BY INTELLIGENT TESTER</testtitle>
<content6 releasenbr="1">
<atten3>
<ptxt>This test should always be performed with at least 2 people.</ptxt>
</atten3>
<test1>
<ptxt>Connect the intelligent tester to the DLC3.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Start the engine and turn the intelligent tester on.</ptxt>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Enter the following items: "DIAGNOSIS / OBD/MOBD / ECT / ACTIVE TEST / SHIFT".</ptxt>
<atten4>
<ptxt>Comparing the shift position commanded by the ACTIVE TEST with the actual shift position enables you to confirm the problem (See page <xref label="Seep01" href="RM000000O8L020X"/>). </ptxt>
<table pgwide="1">
<tgroup cols="3">
<colspec colname="COL1" colwidth="1.77in"/>
<colspec colname="COL2" colwidth="3.54in"/>
<colspec colname="COL3" colwidth="1.77in"/>
<thead>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Item</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Test Details</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>Diagnostic Note</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</thead>
<tbody>
<row>
<entry valign="middle" align="center">
<ptxt>SHIFT</ptxt>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>[Test Details]</ptxt>
<ptxt>Operate the shift solenoid valve and set each shift position by yourself.</ptxt>
<ptxt>[Others]</ptxt>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>Press "←" button: Shift up</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>Press "→" button: Shift down</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</entry>
<entry valign="middle">
<ptxt>Possible to check the operation of the shift solenoid valves.</ptxt>
</entry>
</row>
</tbody>
</tgroup>
</table>
</atten4>
<atten3>
<list1 type="unordered">
<item>
<ptxt>This test can be conducted when the vehicle is stopped.</ptxt>
</item>
<item>
<ptxt>When shifting gears using the Active Test function, do not operate the accelerator pedal for 2 seconds before and after shifting gears.</ptxt>
</item>
</list1>
</atten3>
<atten4>
<ptxt>The shift position commanded by the TCM is shown in the DATA LIST/SHIFT display on the intelligent tester.</ptxt>
</atten4>
</test1>
<test1>
<ptxt>Check the vehicle speed and the gear position when the engine speed is 1,000 rpm.</ptxt>
<atten4>
<ptxt>Because the torque converter clutch has not engaged, it may be difficult to obtain the speeds specified in 4th, 5th, and 6th gear, however a difference of speed should still be evident following each gear change.</ptxt>
</atten4>
